# This directory is the staging queue for cataloging.
#
# Files acquired via /api/upload, the MCP `acquire_for_catalog` tool, or
# direct git push land here first. The catalog workflow (.github/workflows/
# catalog.yml) promotes one file at a time from here to static/originals/,
# runs the catalog, and at the end promotes the next file in FIFO order.
#
# This serializes catalog work without needing a cron schedule: throughput
# is bounded only by how fast each catalog run completes. With one file in
# the queue, it drains in one promotion. With twenty files, it drains in
# twenty promotions, one after another.
#
# Cancellation: deleting a file from raw/queue/ before it's promoted
# prevents it from ever being cataloged. The Acquisition page surfaces
# files in this directory as PENDING and offers a checkbox to remove them.
#
# Files in this directory are NOT visible on the Quartz site (raw/ is
# excluded from the build).
